    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "it looks like the first example you give is a bug. as for your last question\n- `df.xs('blah', level=2) = df.xs('blah', level=2) * 2` is not syntactically valid python.\n- all of the other methods look valid except that in place assignment might be slightly more efficient here.\n- `ix` tries to be smart about integer vs labelled indexing\n- `loc` only allows labelled indexing\n- `iloc` only allows integer indexing\n\n[here](http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/indexing.html) is the documentation for the indexers\n"
